{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "06", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "58", "S": "56"}}, "news": [{"title": "Ahmedabad civic body puts parking onus on property owners", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has implemented strict new parking regulations, placing the onus on property owners to manage vehicle parking within their premises. Non-compliance risks building usage permission suspension, with owners now responsible for preventing street parking and ensuring clear, marked bays. Buildings must also remove obstructions and submit annual self-declarations regarding parking area integrity.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ahmedabad-civic-body-enforces-new-parking-regulations-on-property-owners/130049159?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-197336/130049159.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "PMRDA seeks clarity from Maharashtra govt on Maan-Mhalunge town planning scheme execution", "para": "PMRDA seeks state clarity on executing the Maan-Mhalunge Town Planning Scheme (TPS-1) following Mhalunge's merger with PMC. The 250-hectare project, initiated by PMRDA in 2017, is nearing implementation, with landowners urging speedy approval for planned development in the Hinjewadi-Maan-Mhalunge corridor.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/pmrda-seeks-decision-from-maharashtra-govt-on-maan-mhalunge-town-planning-scheme/130049146?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-15292/130049146.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Developer cannot take extra charge for PNG connections: Green Gas", "para": "Green Gas Limited has clarified that residents will not face additional charges for piped natural gas connections. This comes after a real e